metadata.name: White Night Vol.1 #222
metadata.description:
I have a long-term photography project called “White Night”, which explores special images of trees through black and white inversion.

I attempt to generate similar images by code, and this is the start of the journey.

Made with p5js.

Controls:
- Press “f” to toggle the frame, there is my signature on the mat inside the frame.
- Press “s” to save the image displayed at that moment as a PNG file.
- Change the canvas size by adding “size” URL parameter, for example: &size=1000 (you may add this and lower the number if your device can’t render properly)

metadata.name: Sky Imagination #91
metadata.description:
It is an interactive piece created with p5.js that allows the viewer to imagine different things as they watch the clouds and colors of the sky converge and change. 
The artwork aims to evoke the feeling of wonder and curiosity, 
inviting the viewer to explore their imagination and discover new possibilities.

metadata.description: This city was one of the most beautiful cities in the world, but after the war, it turned into ruins and hell, and the whole city was engulfed in smoke.

metadata.name: Strata Lines #17
metadata.description:
Lines in black and white that emulate rock strata formation.
The parameters are randomly selected from a pool of 32 hand picked combinations for the spread, width and scale.

Each piece is unique.

Coded with p5js.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2021

metadata.name: Bored Man #62
metadata.description: One hundred bored men stored permanently and immutably on the blockchain until the heat death of the universe.

metadata.name: Farbteiler #125
metadata.description: Each Farbteiler is a rectilinear, mostly self-avoiding walk, dividing the space of the canvas with dotted grids using colors from Johannes Itten's Farbkreis. Everything is inside and everything is outside.

metadata.name: Emergence #64
metadata.description:
Using different noise techniques this work is an exploration of the emergence of complex and organic structures from seemingly random noise. The resemblance to ferrofluids and organic "cells" leads to interesting and almost hypnotic visual effects that evolve indefinitely.

Black and white is the most common feature but there are 5 more colour palettes possible. The parameters are hand picked and selected randomly from a pool, every drop is unique.

Press,
"s" to save a screenshot in 4k
"p" to switch to black and white
"space" to pause
"left arrow" to step back
"right arrow" to step forward

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Flossom #73
metadata.description: This work is a research of flow fields, exploring generative art forms and colors. It uses various drawing methods, randomized color palettes, and layers of patterns to add multiple dimensions of variety to the work. Willing to create a visual blossom.

metadata.name: A Distant Memory #295
metadata.description:
A distant memory of trees, buildings and the old village. Once a moment, the memory is illuminated by a beam of light, which gives me the insight of this work.

--------------------

This is an abstract generation made by pure code.

--------------------

In live mode, press 's' or 'S' to save a high resolution png.

Please be patient with drawing process (it'll take one minute in my computer).
This is my last artwork in 2022. I hope you like this work.

Endlessworld 2022

metadata.name: Shift #12
metadata.description:
A generative algorithm honing the power of vertical displacement.

How simple may a generative algorithm be while simultaneously staying diverse enough for each art piece to be truly unique? Shift is the result of an exploration into this space, basing its existence on two principles — dissection and vertical shifting. Each variable in this art engine has been meticulously weighted, giving rise to high diversity and the possibility of epic combinations. 

Shift is a series of 888 unique pieces.

############

Display resolution is 1000x1400. Press ’s’ (in live mode) to generate a 6000x8400 hi-res image. This may take a while to generate depending on your hardware.

Original artwork by perkwerk * made with p5.js * 2022
